a. small, fast-acting
b. made in axon terminal
c. amino acids or related compounds
2. neuropeptides
a. large (many amino acids)
b. made in cell body, stored in dense-core vesicles in the axon terminal
(1) one or more may be released along with a classical nt
c. some act like classical nts
d. most are neuromodulators
(1) don't cause EPSPs/IPSPs
(2) cause long term changes in synapse
