- responsible for exchanges between plasma and interstitial fluid (solute exchange mainly by diffusion)
1. thin-walled, narrow vessels
2. highly branched
3. blood flows slowly through individual vessels
4. lipid soluble substances pass through cells $\left(\mathrm{O}_{2}, \mathrm{CO}_{2}\right)$
