1. rings of smooth muscle can block flow through capillaries in less active tissues
a. sensitive to local metabolic changes
- fluid shifts and bulk flow
1. important in distribution of fluids between plasma and interstitial fluid
a. fluid (not proteins) pushed out through pores at arteriolar end (ultrafiltration)
(1) capillary blood pressure exceeds plasma-colloid osmotic pressure (oncotic pressure - force drawing water toward plasma proteins)
b. fluid reabsorbed at venular end
(1) capillary BP lower than plasma-colloid osmotic pressure
2. and, ultrafiltration occurs in open capillaries, reabsorption in closed capillaries
